{"title":"Tecnologías de monitoreo y tratamiento en diabetes","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Endocrinología/Tecnologías de monitoreo y tratamiento en diabetes-2024-1.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Tecnologías de monitoreo y\\Ntratamiento en diabetes","guid":"rJDr8fIKfo75hvA7Hg5bpg","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Evolución\\NTecnológica:","guid":"qIjw6OdOXGZSUdnwudNoNw","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"1. Década de 1970:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• Introducción del infusor continuo subcutáneo de insulina (ICSI) → conocido como bomba de insulina.","guid":"laTTZglU2dP6bY8mozrO-w","children":[]}]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"2. Década de 1980:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"5","parent":"4","text":"• Desarrollo del monitoreo continuo de glucosa (MCG) → permite medir glicemia intersticial de manera continua.","guid":"l4XwNYuEA6zLsG2b_D4NUA","children":[]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"3. Evolución de MCG:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"• Inicialmente: Uso retrospectivo, solicitado por el médico.","guid":"7mJdmOxQlHPftUBuw0TkdA","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"• Avance: Monitoreo en tiempo real (MCG-TR).","guid":"m7fgpWAsoIy5JTe8SeNXPg","children":[]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"1","text":"4. Última Década:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"• Integración de ICSI y MCG en un solo dispositivo → Terapia de Bomba Sensor-Aumentada (SAPT).","guid":"7VEqGCoJpwPcWkF21U28Ig","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"9","text":"• Inicialmente: Sin suspensión automática ante hipoglicemia.","guid":"ICYbdx6XDkFpIFWpPytENw","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"9","text":"• Avance: Modelos SAPT con interrupción automática de insulina ante predicción de hipoglicemia.","guid":"MANl4xNbT2OKbhAGwsVjBQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"1","text":"Páncreas\\NArtificial:","guid":"PiA7Rg60zpgQcYA_odBFOw","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"1. Concepto:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"15","parent":"14","text":"• Programa computacional → aumenta/disminuye insulina según niveles de glicemia (MCG).","guid":"4-XD0PWGeZPs6DL25u5eAA","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"13","text":"Beneficios:","guid":"0AKPfyO7SdjhjOf7VfpKnA","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"1. Mejor control metabólico.","guid":"aPRZV4dLOxmDJAA50OqtKQ","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"16","text":"2. Disminución de hipoglicemia severa.","guid":"CWO5n7NrK4RnKZwGWkjCeA","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"19","parent":"0","text":"Infusor Continuo Subcutáneo de Insulina\\N(ICSI):","guid":"sXI5fc1c2EVm8hFjNVr3Gw","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"• Descripción:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"• Dispositivo electrónico → entrega insulina de forma continua al tejido subcutáneo.","guid":"U7XVvvvcEV5A3ctK6G__BQ","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"• Reservorio de insulina ultrarrápida → absorción estable y rápida.","guid":"pe9CwtoOJudulQ1lBcbusQ","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"20","text":"• Sustituye la secreción fisiológica basal del páncreas durante ayuno e interprandial.","guid":"FrmbK6xUI-dwdlUyg66FvQ","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"20","text":"• En pacientes con MDI → reemplaza insulina de acción prolongada.","guid":"_2sLyo76P9oOlPutCj38Yw","children":[]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"19","text":"• Funcionamiento:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"• Infusión basal programada por el especialista según requerimientos horarios ","guid":"vyDvpsTyQvkq06BYeUj95A","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"25","text":"• Insulina para comidas y corrección de hiperglicemia → bolos","guid":"-ChJ-JLSSE5Ssw6WumoLGw","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"25","text":"• Paciente ingresa datos de glicemia e hidratos de carbono.","guid":"lniOzbTFNU8XNqG-mXEUgA","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"25","text":"• Programa asistente calcula dosis del bolo según relación insulina/hidrato de carbono y sensibilidad a insulina.","guid":"Z5pfjT_x5GW_f-nwfk52Zw","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"25","text":"• Considera insulina activa del último bolo → entrega dosis precisas.","guid":"0viUNdwq8KND5QcZBYmbaw","children":[]}]},{"id":"31","parent":"19","text":"• Ventajas","guid":"2ViyNzzYDP0r0VuxQ8q1cg","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"• Administración a través de catéter → múltiples dosis sin inyecciones.","guid":"nkxSazgu10uBTeVxZjoDQg","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"31","text":"• Dosis diferenciada a lo largo del día.","guid":"USYLdnNUvncVV8F_jQesWQ","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"31","text":"• Posibilidad de dosis pequeñas (0,025 U/h basal, 0,025 U prandial).","guid":"2_HWAgIvlDAuOnTOe_0OJQ","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"31","text":"• Basales temporales para situaciones especiales (ejercicio, enfermedad).","guid":"KfcqOFs6SIUNUPwgH3kPaw","children":[]}]},{"id":"36","parent":"19","text":"• Asistente\\Ncalculador de bolo:","guid":"XhSjwzoZZThnUTVHGUWskg","children":[{"id":"37","parent":"36","text":"• Rango de glicemia meta (día y noche).","guid":"EPXmRRF-RvX_5WAnHTcJqQ","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"36","text":"• Factor de sensibilidad o corrección.","guid":"ktowRxPZO1ZFMmVizK8qQA","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"36","text":"• Ratio insulina/hidrato de carbono.","guid":"0ip--xI2q_rMSRC7tvF1xg","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"36","text":"• Insulina activa.","guid":"DFHCP-xN031YiVqWV1DggA","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"36","text":"• Beneficios:","guid":"ZG4NB6QJfCS5j2B0Q2o3eg","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"• Mejor control metabólico.","guid":"FS3S60NVDEUZn_xeGokhpg","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"41","text":"• Fácil tratamiento de hipoglicemia.","guid":"Ro9A7WkPmLntUWEGe7UPJw","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"41","text":"• Mayor precisión en insulinoterapia.","guid":"Ap2A1_WZzs9iOZgGcmmhqA","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"45","parent":"0","text":"Monitorización Continua\\Nde Glucosa (MCG)","guid":"D_ntjdL2-A4eC0pHqdh0og","children":[{"id":"46","parent":"45","text":"Descripción:","guid":"tVL7aUhHRjHEsINM2pAnNg","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"• MCG:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"• Dispositivo electrónico → mide glucosa intersticial del tejido subcutáneo cada 5 min\\N(288 mediciones diarias).","guid":"y7_jP50Xzyru43TSLRAZ9Q","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"47","text":"• Sensor con glucosa oxidasa → cataliza reacción entre glucosa y O2.","guid":"oQlMmsvD7sUAp7CTOEQmeA","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"47","text":"• Genera corriente eléctrica en nano amperios → enviada inalámbricamente del transmisor al receptor.","guid":"hS1uFSbEPcxqhCZqoNPz8w","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"47","text":"• Algoritmo de calibración → convierte corriente en glicemia (mg/dl).","guid":"km8CX7RZw5fM6oPo9Nfo-w","children":[]}]},{"id":"52","parent":"46","text":"• Sensor:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"• Desechable.","guid":"Wsl8T-zQ3TEEM39KFJ6-bg","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"52","text":"• Vida útil: 3-14 días (según marca).","guid":"y6VNoEFdP3Du5BjJAY8uRw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"45","text":"Funcionamiento:","guid":"HL0akzHgDSjQsNjLcQoIfw","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"• MCG mide glicemia intersticial, no capilar.","guid":"n4Y6DuIq0oswIYgx1QL2Xw","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"55","text":"• Desfase\\Nfisiológico:","guid":"8LAvp9iWITAlk4BNmad3TA","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"• Desfase de 5-15 min entre glucosa capilar e intersticial → difusión de glucosa desde capilar al intersticio hasta el sensor.","guid":"OlaDbQqCgmarSUkP5aB9tw","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"57","text":"• Retraso en medición de glucosa intersticial durante cambios rápidos de glicemia en sangre.","guid":"AQp230ihJ5bbRLtxl3XSzw","children":[]}]},{"id":"60","parent":"55","text":"• Diferencia media respecto a glicemia capilar: 11-14% en sensores modernos.","guid":"1xeU4LrczSpHZR_tCXi4Bw","children":[]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"45","text":"Monitores de\\NGlucosa (MCG):","guid":"EjpxW_jNPUebsC6oIsFyjw","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"• MCG Profesional:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"63","parent":"62","text":"• Ej.: Ipro (Medtronics®), Freestyle Libre Pro (Abbott®).","guid":"L6RAJktcDLGeU2SkcV2fpg","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"62","text":"• Lecturas ciegas, utilizado como examen “holter”.","guid":"SN3QdqHPRTbPgVXz4QNjXg","children":[]}]},{"id":"65","parent":"61","text":"• MCG-TR o personal sin\\Ninfusor continuo:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"66","parent":"65","text":"• Ej.: G4 Platinum (Dexcom®), G5 Mobile (Dexcom®).","guid":"z-uJPI5TK1qB3CirvebUGQ","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"65","text":"• Pantalla con niveles de glicemia, alarmas programables, calibración 2-4 veces al día.","guid":"-b7O6BNkh9UZTOJg10vW3g","children":[]}]},{"id":"68","parent":"61","text":"• MCG-TR o personal integrado con\\Ninfusor continuo (SAPT):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"• Ej.: Paradigm VEO (Medtronics®), MiniMed 640G (Medtronics®).","guid":"d18hz6JRCZ4YdhejtVitog","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"68","text":"• Integración con ICSI, alarmas programables, calibración 2-4 veces al día.","guid":"yDFRT-l6qGzXG0iIemMd3A","children":[]}]},{"id":"71","parent":"61","text":"• MCG con\\Nsistema Flash:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"72","parent":"71","text":"• Ej.: Freestyle Libre (Abbott®).","guid":"YPnvoNalpBl8juuZv8RCSg","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"71","text":"• Lecturas en tiempo real, sin receptor gráfico continuo, sin alarmas programables.","guid":"8wubvTc_VHZuDrpEcI7oiw","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"74","parent":"0","text":"Sensor-Augmented Pump Therapy\\N(SAPT)","guid":"gmwGpD1OTGM1e4heU-Znfg","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"Descripción:","guid":"BhscZ6OL19-Pj1-f2Ok0Cg","children":[{"id":"76","parent":"75","text":"• SAPT:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"• Integración de ICSI y MCG en un solo dispositivo ","guid":"TpCS6-R3dAU3n-iwtfmA9A","children":[]}]},{"id":"78","parent":"75","text":"• Algoritmo computacional → detención automática de insulina ante hipoglicemia o antes de que ocurra, y reinicio posterior.","guid":"ZkRAnWTabHUOaqJH6vUpQQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"79","parent":"74","text":"Funcionamiento:","guid":"PLnp9Hb_8xvSvkkzofHIJA","children":[{"id":"80","parent":"79","text":"• Modelos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"• Algunos reinician infusión tras 2 horas de suspensión.","guid":"2NBIuIqBB2AjXlKlRvuPyA","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"80","text":"• Otros reinician cuando glicemia regresa a niveles seguros.","guid":"saV8rgOHfvhyp3bVB9PUuQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"83","parent":"79","text":"• Umbrales de glicemia programados individualmente.","guid":"LEmho8vVSqi4dl63FpejCg","children":[]}]},{"id":"84","parent":"74","text":"Seguridad:","guid":"39ji6dI7W4WU8a673ID4oA","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"• Auto-suspensión:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"86","parent":"85","text":"• Demostrada como segura (12-14).","guid":"9qnM_QYuUqNOwNd5pxjCeQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"87","parent":"74","text":"Infusores:","guid":"XlfI3Q0BQ6z69-_P-Lrh8g","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"• ICSI Estándar:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"• Ej.: Paradigm 515/715 (Medtronics®), Accu-Chek Combo (Roche®).","guid":"Pb5WbtdV7EJ_TF80_-M1Ow","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"88","text":"• Sin MCG continuo, comunicación inalámbrica opcional, algunos modelos impermeables.","guid":"H4DWHr9sABqt_xric2m0fg","children":[]}]},{"id":"91","parent":"87","text":"• ICSI tipo “parche”:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"92","parent":"91","text":"• Ej.: Omnipod (InsuletCorp®).","guid":"IQ0XrgUIWWc_kZYuSU1ONQ","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"91","text":"• Reservorio desechable, cánula integrada, adherido a la piel, control remoto inalámbrico, resistente al agua.","guid":"xPK2rPRXQtRKnfopbHTcxw","children":[]}]},{"id":"94","parent":"87","text":"• “Sensor-Augmented Pump\\NTherapy” sin auto-suspensión:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"95","parent":"94","text":"• Ej.: Vibe (Animas®), T:Slim G4 (Tandem®).","guid":"xlLHvDyJ7t8XCOlCirmmjw","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"94","text":"• Integración con MCG-TR, alarmas programables, no modifica infusión ante hipo/hiperglicemia.","guid":"OI4lAYbehScc4enig0TqpQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"97","parent":"87","text":"• “Sensor-Augmented Pump\\NTherapy” con auto-suspensión:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"• Ej.: Paradigm Veo (Medtronics®), Minimed 640G (Medtronics®).","guid":"A81K_4OrVVVjY1s-WLjurg","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"97","text":"• Comunicación entre infusor y MCG, suspensión y reinicio de insulina ante hipoglicemia.","guid":"2sGRkmo-1JdFocqJiTFyFA","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"0","text":"Páncreas Artificial (PA) y\\NSistema Híbrido","guid":"yeWb0TiNw8A0odjYH8i8Tw","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"Descripción:","guid":"XnxnJpEA77vXkLJPZYROnw","children":[{"id":"102","parent":"101","text":"• PA (biónico o\\Nclosed-loop):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"103","parent":"102","text":"• Insulina entregada al subcutáneo por catéter (igual que ICSI).","guid":"G-Je9JfsnXR6XIfUgJgXsw","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"102","text":"• Integración con MCG → cierre del circuito (closed-loop).","guid":"F3_drTSWIM2CTxyZAqo7OQ","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"102","text":"• Infusor ajusta insulina basal según MCG.","guid":"r5iJKz09dqvcmJk68UhPZA","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"102","text":"• Paciente informa sobre ingesta (habitual, mayor, menor) → sin contar carbohidratos ni medir glicemia capilar.","guid":"OGfQaQ59jMD9HYScsoHXkQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"107","parent":"101","text":"• Sistema Híbrido\\N(MiniMed 670G):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"108","parent":"107","text":"• Integración de sensor e infusor.","guid":"fr9dltPsXV1TF63PvbIvAQ","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"107","text":"• Ajuste automático de insulina basal.","guid":"SMhXFLK8VcJNsZfFFtpgww","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"107","text":"• Paciente debe ejecutar bolos, contar carbohidratos y medir glicemia capilar.","guid":"mCL0beqdVTNvyIACPXNEeA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"100","text":"Limitaciones:","guid":"OF-a2Hs9lK8qn6HFUkoQXA","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"• No idéntico a un páncreas humano:","guid":"LfqxCiffNLXlqMbzlfLXXQ","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"• Insulina entregada a nivel subcutáneo, no portal.","guid":"2WjMTIrR_dVi4uC7XQjf0A","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"111","text":"• Demora en absorción de insulina ultrarrápida.","guid":"GbQBZ0sxJTrbgvkSa_kmXw","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"111","text":"• Imprecisión de sensores de glicemia intersticial vs capilar.","guid":"qvCwXqOXgyQiSUOGN469QQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"116","parent":"100","text":"Beneficios:","guid":"LaLtDAcolU4-amO0fula2g","children":[{"id":"117","parent":"116","text":"• Disminución de hipoglicemia.","guid":"R3S95boYwhdrH8I_aD4B5w","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"116","text":"• Mejoría del control metabólico (comparado con SAPT).","guid":"eQR-LwSTBzIMAV5drSG8qQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"119","parent":"0","text":"• Sistemas bihormonales (insulina y glucagón)\\N→ control por algoritmos separados.","guid":"DEXcvL0ZFdpTGmvgT1TwgA","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"• Estudios iniciales → solo insulina.","guid":"9Cu2u579Emgq_cA0ztC_eA","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"119","text":"Estudios:","guid":"IgXlSAJDZNtwK3YkWEYmgw","children":[{"id":"122","parent":"121","text":"• Inicialmente en pacientes hospitalizados → mejor ajuste de algoritmos.","guid":"pV71iQskC54hlCjlNGqC3g","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"121","text":"• Estudios recientes en sujetos ambulatorios.","guid":"0FTyOxa2QvrUS-P9O5vpyg","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"121","text":"• Al menos 18 dispositivos en estudio (1ra, 2da, y 3ra generación) →\\Nvarían en automatización, control de glicemia y liberación hormonal.","guid":"pe77ZleB9tppdxy-UvVm1Q","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"125","parent":"0","text":"ICSI","guid":"avSXAML44OwtiiR0B0-bhw","children":[{"id":"126","parent":"125","text":"Características\\Ndel Paciente:","guid":"O67svpPsr_6Ib8e0kmolXg","children":[{"id":"127","parent":"126","text":"• Adherencia a insulinoterapia basal-bolo con múltiples inyecciones diarias (≥ 4/día).","guid":"iDjKbwg0jNDDQmftv92a8Q","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"126","text":"• Control frecuente de glicemias capilares (≥ 4/día).","guid":"OzzrxRs16-Dt5dvYELqdkg","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"126","text":"• Motivación para alcanzar buen control metabólico.","guid":"iQuEZ4Ji9QnOB1l73tR-ww","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"126","text":"• Compromiso con terapia compleja y demandante inicialmente.","guid":"q1YNlPHgnHEyLHxF590-iA","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"126","text":"• Conocimiento de conceptos básicos de insulinoterapia basal-bolo.","guid":"_oztfDKdQKbYMuIsWE_y1Q","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"126","text":"• Dominio en conteo de carbohidratos.","guid":"-OK8ZxXSMVoSDxBs8pyQhA","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"126","text":"• Conocimiento y aplicación de relación insulina/carbohidratos y factor de sensibilidad.","guid":"s0VskjahFCaPriI-Q71wRQ","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"126","text":"• Capacidad de ajuste en insulinoterapia.","guid":"2zL79gBYAg_A1Y0qwx6IpQ","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"126","text":"• Buena adherencia a citaciones y control médico.","guid":"mk5IhFdSOqM7zFG2k5OeyQ","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"126","text":"• Contacto frecuente con equipo de salud experto, en centros de referencia.","guid":"amON9EJpUwadoiiy2ilYFg","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"126","text":"• Ausencia de patología psiquiátrica no compensada.","guid":"Mqx2VVdivTvtzc4PHvJb9A","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"126","text":"• Expectativas realistas de la terapia con ICSI.","guid":"XVbNExAfoiQ3cl-aT6k_ig","children":[]}]},{"id":"139","parent":"125","text":"Características del\\NEquipo Tratante:","guid":"POvgnztQgS0hMGLPvbMWQg","children":[{"id":"140","parent":"139","text":"• Entrenamiento y experiencia en tecnología en diabetes.","guid":"0MJX3ARclu37lYjbtnGh1g","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"139","text":"• Conocimiento y dominio de equipos comercialmente disponibles.","guid":"wYqSSWuqgwxxrcAWf9ROqQ","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"139","text":"• Equipo multidisciplinario (enfermera y nutricionista) con especialización en entrenamiento avanzado en diabetes.","guid":"l8sEfGA3E5qwPOv18d0acg","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"139","text":"• Programa estructurado de entrenamiento y control de pacientes usuarios de tecnología.","guid":"C7BP0k-Jt_kASZBOXWXJFQ","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"139","text":"• Accesibilidad 24 h para asistencia médica (al menos primeros 15 días).","guid":"7aJkMqGTzs2JXWECwaf4_A","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"139","text":"• Disponibilidad horaria para controles ambulatorios (al menos 5 días/semana).","guid":"Lm1WJy1g6gS5xRvOanf4qA","children":[]}]},{"id":"146","parent":"125","text":"Transición de\\NMDI a ICSI:","guid":"jCvmda1-LXE_YPXGZ7w-fA","children":[{"id":"147","parent":"146","text":"• Revisado recientemente (3).","guid":"XN_EzEs23UGBozcJv3pHnA","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"146","text":"• Pacientes\\Nadecuados:","guid":"97rvBQFLCLgk-UxKwAuj4A","children":[{"id":"149","parent":"148","text":"• Alta motivación y compromiso.","guid":"lSnzscG_w4c0QxAyYjzZTQ","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"148","text":"• Conocimiento y entrenamiento avanzado en diabetes.","guid":"enTPulDQln_s3BFHHvX5Ig","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"148","text":"• Edad no es limitante.","guid":"Tw3ayVuGW7Qeo0B_KjTBAQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"152","parent":"146","text":"• Consideraciones\\Nlogísticas:","guid":"ljNLlCAFQAIomPoH1Lzwwg","children":[{"id":"153","parent":"152","text":"• Experiencia del equipo tratante.","guid":"y_qlevY_Uky84TjIMKd39w","children":[]},{"id":"154","parent":"152","text":"• Necesidad de controles frecuentes al inicio.","guid":"J9W4xE6qGCmUUQRNh2HE6w","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"152","text":"• Disponibilidad de insumos y soporte técnico continuo.","guid":"0ctE16dQ1Zo8m7wpXQMKig","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"156","parent":"125","text":"Indicaciones\\Nde uso:","guid":"nibR9uGOnCQaY-UVvux9Vg","children":[{"id":"157","parent":"156","text":"• Variabilidad glicémica.","guid":"WbgnTMBdMy3pgnpK-G95rA","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"156","text":"• Hipoglicemia severa.","guid":"cHapJxuBCxE0MH8Y_0StsQ","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"156","text":"• Falta de control metabólico óptimo.","guid":"oNRuuT95qx4zIpDBflHntg","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"156","text":"• Compromiso con el tratamiento ","guid":"isezfbWIu1DOZjxQ4uLgnw","children":[]}]},{"id":"161","parent":"125","text":"Beneficios\\Ndel ICSI:","guid":"v5FYRljDPyOCuXLZYptAbw","children":[{"id":"162","parent":"161","text":"1. Mejor control\\Nmetabólico:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"163","parent":"162","text":"• Meta-análisis: Reducción de HbA1c en adultos con DM1:","guid":"Ez7fwUeo7D9NiSDICEE9eQ","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"162","text":"• ICSI vs MDI: -0, 3% (promedio).","guid":"Bkcc2MFUsxZUxdPXjSiokw","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"162","text":"• SAPT vs MDI: -0, 68% (22-23).","guid":"sZDMK7P0VcX7CA7es3fMMA","children":[]}]},{"id":"166","parent":"161","text":"2. Reducción de hipoglicemia severa\\N(HS):","guid":"MgauFFN8BjRAkQKSSTS2Qw","children":[{"id":"167","parent":"166","text":"• Disminución de HS y HS inducida por ejercicio (24-26).","guid":"Vfe8TEVT8T_s6BZch3yh0A","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"166","text":"• Uso de SAPT con suspensión automática recomendado en HS recurrentes (27-29).","guid":"OnY4pqmx2x89mLY6WkMOSw","children":[]}]},{"id":"169","parent":"161","text":"3. Mejoría en\\Ncalidad de vida:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"170","parent":"169","text":"• Impacto positivo comparado con MDI (22-23).","guid":"0xTBeYaj6K1tSwr4KIii1g","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"169","text":"• Baja tasa de suspensión del ICSI por los pacientes (2-11%) (31-32).","guid":"wDuuYPVR9gEpr6LlLtfY8g","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"172","parent":"125","text":"Desventajas del ICSI:","guid":"WWV9kl8jnb0PfuFljHIyWQ","children":[{"id":"173","parent":"172","text":"1. Falla del set\\Nde infusión:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"174","parent":"173","text":"• Problemas: Oclusión del catéter, desplazamiento de la cánula, filtración de insulina,\\Nburbujas de aire, acodamiento del catéter/cánula.","guid":"H13c6BLbHPnm2nUtN76_YA","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"173","text":"• Frecuencia: Mayor cuando no se cumplen recomendaciones de instalación y cuidado.","guid":"yHvt7Z_7OWlkiumpt_JUww","children":[]}]},{"id":"176","parent":"172","text":"2. Hiperglicemia, cetosis y\\Ncetoacidosis diabética (CAD):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"177","parent":"176","text":"• Interrupción de insulina → insulinopenia severa en >60 min.","guid":"Bg0IAbnF_ccR0EDZE5Zslg","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"176","text":"• Elevación de glicemia y formación de cuerpos cetónicos → CAD en pocas horas (33-34).","guid":"Mm7Lqqh2QgXDS0DpchYRkA","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"176","text":"• Incidencia de CAD no mayor que con MDI en ICSI modernos (35).","guid":"sK4YBUxy7ii6Z9-u3xzo9w","children":[]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"172","text":"3. Infecciones cutáneas y\\Notros eventos adversos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"181","parent":"180","text":"• Infecciones en sitio de infusión → disminución sustancial, casi inexistente (38-39).","guid":"lNQGXP1ECePeXi7s4FqKiw","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"180","text":"• Lipohipertrofia: 26% de usuarios (37).","guid":"Iq0RZcaVvp_Adiqu2m6AlA","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"180","text":"• Irritación/alergia a adhesivos y hiperpigmentación.","guid":"OjLeVl1_q_gnamiBDJZsyw","children":[]}]},{"id":"184","parent":"172","text":"4. Costos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"185","parent":"184","text":"• Costo del dispositivo y insumos permanentes.","guid":"zPw0xPNHXBjYGwZN4SIywQ","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"184","text":"• Costo-efectividad demostrado al analizar control metabólico, menor HS,\\Nprevención de complicaciones crónicas y calidad de vida (40-44).","guid":"Bhx3OR5RqqzgqIAEIoCnHA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"187","parent":"125","text":"Priorización ","guid":"","children":[{"id":"188","parent":"187","text":"1° Prioridad: Pacientes\\Ncon DM Tipo 1","guid":"xoiYpEvaglS-J5jo6v7w-g","children":[{"id":"189","parent":"188","text":"• I. Hipoglicemia severa repetitiva y/o asintomática.","guid":"qIhhpjGjbGRIJ57YcQPv0w","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"188","text":"• II. Alta variabilidad glicémica.","guid":"bXURfoCI9X0NNJOIcYpqyw","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"188","text":"• III. Tratamiento con dosis pequeñas y alta insulinosensibilidad.","guid":"wAZ6SK2CZXKSTjVnPdSQfA","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"188","text":"• IV. Poblaciones especiales (embarazo, niños, atletas de alto rendimiento).","guid":"MP_hL75o3zDLgO3oJYvC_Q","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"188","text":"• V. Falta de control metabólico óptimo pese a esfuerzos.","guid":"tEDpkTuuhzIsV875t4i5-Q","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"188","text":"• VI. Fenómeno del alba.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"188","text":"• VII. Gastroparesia.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"188","text":"• VIII. Pacientes que consideran útil la bomba para alcanzar objetivos glicémicos.","guid":"_B07uLsLWSbpROuHGpat6A","children":[]}]},{"id":"197","parent":"187","text":"2° Prioridad: Pacientes con DM\\NTipo 2 Seleccionados","guid":"lP0gOx9BHfaSLK8dEVVa2Q","children":[{"id":"198","parent":"197","text":"• Tratamiento intensificado con MDI sin alcanzar control metabólico.","guid":"qGLeSuBhWDXvwZOBbVorSQ","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"197","text":"• Estilo de vida/horario impredecible (trabajo en turnos, viajes frecuentes).","guid":"L-C2OXYwkcMYagkj785JRg","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"197","text":"• Insulinoresistencia severa.","guid":"2Jp81e3nkysrlYSoplaeBg","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"197","text":"• Fenómeno del alba.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"202","parent":"187","text":"3° Prioridad: Pacientes con Otros Tipos de Diabetes","guid":"IAqLD9PDHn6VeYqVitSgxw","children":[{"id":"203","parent":"202","text":"• Ejemplo: Post-pancreatectomía.","guid":"cmSQJqbs129BSHzs7RzsZA","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"204","parent":"0","text":"MCG","guid":"kl99r4g05CvCQ7PLkZu6Tg","children":[{"id":"205","parent":"204","text":"Beneficios","guid":"byoQMYfPJoR32mAWqS_Pwg","children":[{"id":"206","parent":"205","text":"1. Mejor Control\\NMetabólico:","guid":"dL8tDj-6ZDHylRMTxEZQmg","children":[{"id":"207","parent":"206","text":"• Reducción de HbA1c:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"208","parent":"207","text":"• MCG-TR vs auto monitoreo con glicemia capilar (45-47).","guid":"uJDXApnz1Xm_3KfIVK6ZcA","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"207","text":"• Mejoría directa con uso del sensor ≥ 60-70% del tiempo.","guid":"jAxPE0_uvKsUMgTkvW-d5A","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"207","text":"• Beneficio notable en pacientes con ICSI.","guid":"JBvuGZHO1eJDRi51bZ3b7Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"211","parent":"206","text":"• Estudio en curso para MCG-TR con MDI (DIaMonD).","guid":"bDmUKIYQLrvcCobCh5kfxw","children":[]}]},{"id":"212","parent":"205","text":"2. Reducción de\\NHipoglicemia Severa (HS):","guid":"qdtTKhCXRKGZUw-twdRYIQ","children":[{"id":"213","parent":"212","text":"• SAPT con MCG-TR:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"214","parent":"213","text":"• Reducción significativa en tasa, duración y severidad de HS.","guid":"Ii6_UpqbJI9Ugnx63EbKGQ","children":[]},{"id":"215","parent":"213","text":"• Sin deterioro del control glicémico (12-14, 27-29).","guid":"1cl-wvJP4lKbUuhDh5J-kA","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"216","parent":"204","text":"Desventajas","guid":"OmnqMwyG163-iblMvDHXAQ","children":[{"id":"217","parent":"216","text":"1. Desfase Fisiológico:","guid":"5C6XPa4yzVFcnu-bHuqsoA","children":[{"id":"218","parent":"217","text":"• Glicemia\\NIntersticial vs\\NCapilar:","guid":"Vb0oSHXEhEfOwb_tUv6t9w","children":[]},{"id":"219","parent":"217","text":"• Desfase frente a\\Nvariaciones > 2 mg/dl/min.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"220","parent":"217","text":"• MCG es complemento, no reemplazo\\Ndel auto monitoreo capilar.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"221","parent":"216","text":"2. Necesidad de\\NCalibraciones Periódicas:","guid":"knndyq2PuvkCHUlEoEDMAA","children":[{"id":"222","parent":"221","text":"• Calibración:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"223","parent":"222","text":"• 2-4 mediciones diarias de glicemia capilar.","guid":"yFMxM8jntBK_SqjdtpkNqA","children":[]}]},{"id":"224","parent":"221","text":"• Excepción: MCG con sistema Flash, calibrado en fábrica (10).","guid":"2dYDyTOTpxQ6sMYohNHzBg","children":[]}]},{"id":"225","parent":"216","text":"3. Instalación y Cambio\\NPeriódico del Sensor:","guid":"Evs7v87A3GprqeJp2h0lbw","children":[{"id":"226","parent":"225","text":"• Adherencia:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"227","parent":"226","text":"• Instalación y cambio del sensor → tarea adicional para pacientes con ICSI.","guid":"6FNiLos4tw6-rDMOewKR3w","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"228","parent":"216","text":"4. Agobio por Exceso\\Nde Información:","guid":"L--7Hu8pnJ8O5PGTz3eYzw","children":[{"id":"229","parent":"228","text":"• Alarmas e Información:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"230","parent":"229","text":"• Exceso de alarmas puede ser cansador.","guid":"B5vCP44Ry47Ez7IRcCGKWA","children":[]}]},{"id":"231","parent":"228","text":"• Recomendación: Personalizar alarmas, mantener solo las más importantes.","guid":"50kDAGG99mhjuDEWsBps3w","children":[]}]},{"id":"232","parent":"216","text":"5. Costos:","guid":"gH0JN9YWFMX4VrPivhaSdQ","children":[{"id":"233","parent":"232","text":"• MCG-TR vs Auto Monitoreo:","guid":"Gz4LwjNnarvbTweX-ktjBQ","children":[{"id":"234","parent":"233","text":"• Costo superior al auto monitoreo con glicemia capilar.","guid":"lcvwLTcLaKBK5MhsRCyRnw","children":[]}]},{"id":"235","parent":"232","text":"• Costo efectividad demostrada en mejor control glicémico y prevención de complicaciones crónicas (48-51).","guid":"E_JU8a22nHQtuFSh94_xDA","children":[]}]}]}]}]},"node_count":235,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Endocrinología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Endocrinología","filename":"Tecnologías de monitoreo y tratamiento en diabetes-2024-1","id":"map_593","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Tecnologías de monitoreo y tratamiento en diabetes-2024-1"}